{"properties":{"genre":"Article","timestamp":"2014-07-25T16:30:34Z","author":["Forlani, Maurício C.","de Sá, Rafael O","Tonini, João Filipe R."],"title":"Data from: A new species of Chiasmocleis (Microhylidae, Gastrophryninae) from the Atlantic Forest of Espírito Santo State, Brazil","host":"Tonini JFR, Forlani MC, de Sá RO (2014) A new species of Chiasmocleis (Microhylidae, Gastrophryninae) from the Atlantic Forest of Espírito Santo State, Brazil. ZooKeys 428: 109-132.","keywords":["Amphibians","systematics","phylogenetics","cryptic species"],"description":"Among Neotropical microhylids, the genus Chiasmocleis is exceptionally diverse. Most species of Chiasmocleis were described in recent years based on external morphology, but recent studies using molecular data did not support the monophyly of the species groups clustered based on feet webbing. Furthermore, a phylogeographic study of C. lacrimae estimated high genetic divergence and low gene flow among populations across small geographic ranges. Increasing the molecular and geographic sampling, and incorporating morphological data, we identified new cryptic species. Herein, we used novel genetic and morphological data to describe a new species of Chiasmocleis.","constituent":["doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/8","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/9","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/10","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/12","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/4","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/11","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/5","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/6","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/7","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/1","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/3","doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t/2"],"identifier_uri":"http://hdl.handle.net/10255/dryad.67060","oai":"oai:datadryad.org:10255/dryad.67060","isReferencedBy":["PMID:25161370","doi:10.3897/zookeys.428.7352"],"node_type":"Record","node_source":"Dryad","doi":"doi:10.5061/dryad.gm41t"}}